---
import Base from '../../layouts/Base.astro';

const description = "Charity care programs at nonprofit hospitals. How to apply, income thresholds, and how to get medical bills reduced or forgiven.";
---

<Base title="Hospital Financial Assistance Programs — CreditCookbook" description="{description}" posterTitle="CHARITY CARE" posterLabel="// 06 — nonprofit hospital obligations">
  <section class="section">
    <div class="container">
      <span class="section-label">// content</span>
      <h2 style="margin-bottom: 24px;">Hospital financial assistance (charity care)</h2>
      <p>Nonprofit hospitals are required by federal law (IRC Section 501(r)) to offer financial assistance programs. If your income is below 400% of the federal poverty level, you may qualify for partial or full bill forgiveness — and most patients never know this exists.</p>

<h3 style="margin-top: 40px;">Income thresholds (2024 FPL)</h3>
<table style="margin-bottom: 32px;">
  <thead>
    <tr><th>Income (% of FPL)</th><th>Typical assistance</th></tr>
  </thead>
  <tbody>
    <tr><td>Below 200%</td><td>100% bill forgiveness</td></tr>
    <tr><td>200-250%</td><td>75-100% reduction</td></tr>
    <tr><td>250-300%</td><td>50-75% reduction</td></tr>
    <tr><td>300-400%</td><td>20-50% reduction</td></tr>
    <tr><td>Above 400%</td><td>Case-by-case (still ask)</td></tr>
  </tbody>
</table>

<h3 style="margin-bottom: 16px;">How to apply</h3>
<ol style="margin-left: 24px; line-height: 2.5; margin-bottom: 32px;">
  <li><strong>Find the policy.</strong> Search "[HOSPITAL NAME] financial assistance policy" — it must be publicly posted by law.</li>
  <li><strong>Download the application.</strong> It's usually a 1-2 page form.</li>
  <li><strong>Gather documents.</strong> You'll need: proof of income (pay stubs, tax return), household size, and the bill you're requesting assistance for.</li>
  <li><strong>Submit before it goes to collections.</strong> Most hospitals pause collections during the application review (30-120 days).</li>
  <li><strong>Follow up in writing.</strong> If approved, get the reduction in writing. If denied, appeal — most hospitals have an appeals process.</li>
</ol>

<div class="card">
  <h4 style="margin-bottom: 12px;">Important</h4>
  <ul style="margin-left: 24px; line-height: 2;">
    <li>Apply BEFORE the bill goes to collections</li>
    <li>Nonprofit = 501(c)(3) — most hospitals are nonprofit</li>
    <li>For-profit hospitals are NOT required to offer charity care</li>
    <li>If denied, appeal — approval rates on appeal are significant</li>
    <li>Charity care is separate from Medicaid — you don't need to be on Medicaid</li>
  </ul>
</div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Base>
